The paper focuses on process mining and data extraction from relational databases, which are topics related to database systems (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of multiple viewpoint models and the application of classical process mining techniques suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also touches on the issue of data security and privacy, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
